UID:neiu-art-design-studio-art-residency-2026-2027@artificialnouveau.github
 .io
DTSTAMP:20260713T104504Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260809
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260810
SUMMARY:Deadline: NEIU Art + Design Studio Art Residency 2026-2027
DESCRIPTION:The NEIU Art + Design Studio Art Residency strives to create vi
 sible connections between Northeastern Illinois University's diverse popul
 ation of art and design students and working artists who embody these iden
 tities\, providing insights and inspiration through a dynamic exchange of 
 ideas and techniques. Visiting Artists should demonstrate a commitment to 
 their artistic practice and an interest in engaging with NEIU's students a
 nd creative community. Each Visiting Artist is awarded an honorarium and h
 as full access for a semester to the NEIU Art + Design facilities specific
  to their project\; over the residency they showcase their work in a publi
 c academic forum\, lead a hands-on workshop\, and participate in a Portfol
 io Review Day for NEIU's Art + Design students. FACILITIES (in the Salme H
 arju Steinberg Fine Arts Center) include a Design Studio with the largest 
 collection of Riso drums at any Chicago university\, a Fab Lab (FDM and re
 sin 3D printers\, large-format CNC router\, vinyl cutters\, laser cutters)
 \, a Ceramic Studio (throwing wheels\, glaze room\, electric and gas kilns
 \, raku area)\, a Letterpress Studio (two Vandercook presses\, metal and w
 ood type)\, a Sculpture Studio (wood shop\, clay modeling and spray painti
 ng areas)\, a Photography Studio (analog and digital\, plus a lighting stu
 dio)\, and fully equipped Painting\, Drawing\, and Printmaking studios. BE
 NEFITS: USD 800 honorarium\; facility access based on project focus (Art +
  Tech\, Ceramics\, Drawing\, Painting\, Photography\, Printmaking\, Sculpt
 ure)\, with supplies requestable subject to approval\; and the opportunity
  to exhibit in a group exhibition in the NEIU Fine Arts Center Gallery. PA
 RTICIPATION: lead a 2-hour hands-on workshop for 15-20 students on a topic
  relevant to the project\; give an hour-long artist talk with Q&A\; and se
 rve as a guest panelist for a day-long portfolio review. KEY DATES: open c
 all 2 June - 9 August\; emailed acceptances in October\; Residency Session
  1 runs 25 January - 14 May and Session 2 runs 30 August - 11 December. Ap
 ply via the JotForm application. Deadline 9 August 2026.\n\nOrganisation: 
 Northeastern Illinois University (NEIU)\, Art + Design Department\nLocatio
 n: Salme Harju Steinberg Fine Arts Center\, Northeastern Illinois Universi
 ty\, Chicago\, Illinois\, United States. In-person\; semester-long access 
 to NEIU facilities.\nAward: USD 800 honorarium\, plus a semester of full a
 ccess to NEIU Art + Design facilities specific to the project (Art + Tech\
 , Ceramics\, Drawing\, Painting\, Photography\, Printmaking\, Sculpture)\;
  supplies can be requested with guidance and approval from Studio Area per
 sonnel. Visiting Artists may also exhibit in a group exhibition in the NEI
 U Fine Arts Center Gallery.\nDuration: One semester. Residency Session 1: 
 25 January - 14 May\; Session 2: 30 August - 11 December.\n\nMore: https:/
 /form.jotform.com/261044627286156?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&ut
 m_medium=referral
URL:https://form.jotform.com/261044627286156?utm_source=artificialnouveaugr
 antdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Salme Harju Steinberg Fine Arts Center\, Northeastern Illinois Uni
 versity\, Chicago\, Illinois\, United States. In-person\; semester-long ac
 cess to NEIU facilities.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:art-shanty-projects-performances-art-actions-2027@artificialnouveau.git
 hub.io
DTSTAMP:20260713T104504Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260709
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260710
SUMMARY:Deadline: Art Shanty Projects 2027: Call for Performances + Art Act
 ions
DESCRIPTION:Art Shanty Projects seeks winter enthusiasts and creative adven
 turers to create performances and art actions for its 2027 Program on Bde 
 Uman (Lake Harriet) in Minneapolis. It invites music-makers\, poets\, buil
 ders\, scientists\, dancers\, puppeteers\, writers\, dreamers\, activists\
 , outdoors-people\, conversationalists\, craftspeople\, storytellers\, and
  more to propose new and innovative ways to engage artistically with the p
 ublic in the social context of a village on a frozen lake (or winter 'beac
 h'\, as climate change may necessitate). ASP has an expansive notion of wh
 at constitutes a performance or art action\, having welcomed dance\, creat
 ive sporting events\, happenings\, carnival games\, music\, roving dance\,
  temporary sculpture\, puppet shows\, artful haircuts\, advice booths\, cl
 imate actions\, and more. NOTE: this call is for PERFORMANCES + ART ACTION
 S only (a separate call exists for shanty artists). Since 2004\, Art Shant
 y Projects has created joyful winter art experiences inspired by pop-up ic
 e fishing villages\, using the frozen lake as a public platform for a temp
 orary creative community with tens of thousands of annual visitors. ASP is
  deeply committed to social\, racial\, gender\, and economic justice and t
 o accessibility (embracing the spirit of the ADA). ELIGIBILITY: everyone i
 s eligible (artists at all career stages)\; applicants need not have exper
 ience with everything asked\, but should show eagerness to engage\, develo
 p new skills\, and stay open to new perspectives. Projects that involve se
 lling anything or the exchange of legal currency will not be accepted. COM
 PENSATION: sliding-scale stipend up to USD 1\,000 plus extensive productio
 n and logistical support. PROGRAM: on-ice every Saturday and Sunday\, 10am
 -4pm\, 16 January to 7 February 2027\; selected artists notified mid-Augus
 t 2026\, with mandatory in-person meetings (at least one team member) star
 ting 10 September 2026. Apply via the Google form (preferred) or the no-Go
 ogle-account alternative. Contact Erin Lavelle\, Artistic Director: progra
 m@artshantyprojects.org. Deadline for proposal submissions: 9 July 2026\, 
 11:59pm CST.\n\nOrganisation: Art Shanty Projects\nLocation: Bde Uman (Lak
 e Harriet)\, Minneapolis\, Minnesota\, United States. On-ice program plus 
 several mandatory in-person meetings in Minneapolis\; in-person participat
 ion required.\nAward: Sliding-scale stipend up to USD 1\,000 (request an a
 mount that fits the project: roughly USD 1\,000 for full-day/most-ambitiou
 s activities\, USD 500 for half-day\, USD 250 for short or one-off/solo/lo
 w-production activities). Plus direct production support\, discounted mate
 rials and resource sharing\, a shared warming shanty\, a hot meal\, snacks
 \, hot beverages\, hand/toe warmers\, one parking space per project\, on-s
 ite medic\, and ASL interpreter/audio describer for the public. No applica
 tion fees.\nDuration: On-ice program every Saturday and Sunday\, 10am-4pm\
 , 16 January to 7 February 2027\, with production meetings and mandatory c
 heck-ins from September 2026 onward.\n\nMore: https://artshantyprojects.or
 g/2027-call-for-performances-art-actions/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugran
 tdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://artshantyprojects.org/2027-call-for-performances-art-actions/?u
 tm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Bde Uman (Lake Harriet)\, Minneapolis\, Minnesota\, United States.
  On-ice program plus several mandatory in-person meetings in Minneapolis\;
  in-person participation required.
END:VEVENT
