SUMMARY:Deadline: KHN Center for the Arts: Artist Residency
DESCRIPTION:The Kimmel Harding Nelson Center for the Arts in Nebraska City 
 hosts up to five concurrent residents (visual artists\, writers\, composer
 s\, and interdisciplinary artists) for two- to eight-week stays\, providin
 g free housing\, a private studio\, and a USD 175/week stipend. Open inter
 nationally. Applications are reviewed twice a year\; the next deadline is 
 1 September 2026 for stays in the following season.\n\nOrganisation: Kimme
 l Harding Nelson Center for the Arts\nLocation: Nebraska City\, Nebraska\,
  United States. Open internationally.\nAward: USD 175/week stipend\, plus 
 free housing and a private studio\, for 2 to 8 weeks. Application fee appl
 ies (small\, via Submittable).\nDuration: Residencies of 2-8 weeks\; appli
 cations reviewed in two annual cycles (1 March and 1 September).\n\nMore: 
 https://www.khncenterforthearts.org/residency?utm_source=artificialnouveau
 grantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.khncenterforthearts.org/residency?utm_source=artificialnouv
 eaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Nebraska City\, Nebraska\, United States. Open internationally.
END:VEVENT
